1.0.0 Â· [source](about:blank/src/std/net/tcp.rs.html#156-158)

Opens a TCP connection to a remote host.

`addr` is an address of the remote host. Anything which implements [`ToSocketAddrs`](trait.ToSocketAddrs.html "trait std::net::ToSocketAddrs") trait can be supplied for the address; see this trait documentation for concrete examples.

If `addr` yields multiple addresses, `connect` will be attempted with each of the addresses until a connection is successful. If none of the addresses result in a successful connection, the error returned from the last connection attempt (the last address) is returned.

##### [Â§](#examples-1)Examples

Open a TCP connection to `127.0.0.1:8080`:

```
use std::net::TcpStream;

if let Ok(stream) = TcpStream::connect("127.0.0.1:8080") {
    println!("Connected to the server!");
} else {
    println!("Couldn't connect to server...");
}
```

